    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThere is no clean way to add logic right after treesitter is attached to a buffer, instead we have to hook our logic into another autocmd and `vim.treesitter.start()`.\r\n\r\nExample: https://github.com/lewis6991/dotfiles/blob/13faceced69a2811773071587d9d1af1c4a7526f/config/nvim/lua/lewis6991/treesitter.lua#L65\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n**TreesitterAttach** and **TreesitterDetach** autocmds.",
    "closed_at": "2023-09-19T14:09:27Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Can you give actual examples what such an autocommand would be used for? As is, I don't really see how it would be useful. The example you show is not compelling, since the three commands in the `FileType` autocommand are logically independent.\r\n\r\n(Treesitter doesn't \"attach\" or \"detach\"; that's something nvim-treesitter invented for their module system. That system was a mistake and is dead now.)",
