            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Just additional notes:\r\n\r\nAs @clason mentioned the \"attach\" and \"detach\" mechanism is from nvim-treesitter's module system, not from neovim core. Although I can find a small piece of [confusing comment saying a TS parser \"attaches\" to the buffer](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter.lua#L98) in the neovim core runtime, which also might cause a slight confusion.\r\n\r\nOne relevant use case I've come across before is to add a hook after a TreeSitter parser is \"attached\" after [(possibly asynchronous) installation of treesitter parsers through the plugin](https://github.com/nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter/blob/v0.9.1/lua/nvim-treesitter/install.lua#L719) is done, because the `highlight` module will call `vim.treesitter.start()` asynchronously and later upon attaching the nvim-treesitter module (not attaching TS parsers, precisely speaking). The OP probably wanted to hook some logic into this event. This would be possible through a sort of **User** `TreesitterAttach` autocmd events, but if so should be done on the nvim-treesitter plugin side.",
